---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Help Center | Agent Tunnel">
    <main class="help-main fade-in">
        <header>
            <img src="https://hosted.inled.es/new-agent-tunnel.png" alt="Logo" width="48" height="48" />
            <h1>🆘 Connection Troubleshooting Guide</h1>
        </header>
        
        <p class="intro">This guide helps you resolve common connection and synchronization issues across different platforms.</p>

        <div class="card">
            <h2><span class="platform-tag">All Platforms</span> 1. SSH Key Rejected</h2>
            <p>If the bridge reports that the SSH key was rejected, you need to manually authorize your Mac's bridge key on the remote machine.</p>
            <p class="highlight">Run this command on your Local Mac Terminal:</p>
            <pre>ssh-copy-id -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa_bridge.pub [user]@[remote-ip]</pre>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <h2><span class="platform-tag">Routers / Embedded</span> 2. SFTP / Mutagen Error</h2>
            <p>If you see <code>sftp-server not found</code> or agent installation failures, the remote device lacks an SFTP server, which Mutagen prefers.</p>
            
            <p class="highlight">For OpenWrt Routers:</p>
            <pre>opkg update && opkg install openssh-sftp-server</pre>
            
            <p class="highlight">For Entware (ASUS, Padavan, etc.):</p>
            <pre>opkg update && opkg install sftp-server</pre>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <h2><span class="platform-tag">Linux Servers</span> 3. Permission & Path Issues</h2>
            <p>Ensure the remote user has write permissions to the destination directory and that the <code>.ssh</code> folder has correct permissions.</p>
            <p class="highlight">Run these commands on the Remote Linux machine:</p>
            <pre>mkdir -p ~/.ssh && chmod 700 ~/.ssh
touch ~/.ssh/authorized_keys && chmod 600 ~/.ssh/authorized_keys</pre>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <h2><span class="platform-tag">macOS Remote</span> 4. Remote Login Setup</h2>
            <p>To connect to another Mac, you must enable Remote Login and ensure the user is in the allowed list.</p>
            <p class="highlight">On the Remote Mac:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Go to <b>System Settings > General > Sharing</b></li>
                <li>Enable <b>Remote Login</b></li>
                <li>Click the (i) icon and ensure your user has access.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <h2><span class="platform-tag">Fallback</span> 5. SSH-Only Mode</h2>
            <p>If Mutagen is incompatible with the remote architecture (e.g., very old ARM/MIPS or missing glibc), the bridge will automatically switch to <b>Direct Command Mode</b>. File syncing will be disabled, but Gemini will still be able to execute commands and manage files via SSH.</p>
        </div>

        <footer>
            <p>Agent Tunnel - Built for Jaime</p>
            <a href="/" class="secondary-btn">Back to Dashboard</a>
        </footer>
    </main>
</Layout>

<style>
    .help-main {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 60px 20px;
        height: 100vh;
        overflow-y: auto;
        width: 100%;
    }

    header {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 20px;
        margin-bottom: 40px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        padding-bottom: 30px;
    }

    h1 {
        color: var(--accent);
        font-size: 32px;
        font-weight: 800;
        margin: 0;
    }

    .intro {
        font-size: 18px;
        color: var(--text-muted);
        margin-bottom: 40px;
    }

    .card {
        background: var(--surface);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 12px;
        padding: 30px;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }

    h2 {
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: 20px;
        margin-top: 0;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 12px;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .platform-tag {
        font-size: 10px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        padding: 4px 8px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 700;
        border: 1px solid var(--accent-muted);
    }

    code {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        background: var(--bg);
        padding: 2px 6px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        color: var(--accent);
    }

    pre {
        background: #000;
        padding: 20px;
        border-radius: 8px;
        overflow-x: auto;
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 14px;
        color: #ddd;
        margin: 15px 0;
    }

    .highlight {
        color: var(--green);
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-top: 20px;
        display: block;
    }

    ul {
        padding-left: 20px;
    }

    li {
        margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    footer {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 60px;
        padding-top: 40px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 20px;
    }

    footer p {
        color: var(--text-muted);
        font-size: 14px;
    }

    .secondary-btn {
        text-decoration: none;
        padding: 12px 24px;
        background: var(--surface);
        color: var(--text);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: var(--radius);
        font-weight: 600;
        transition: 0.2s;
    }

    .secondary-btn:hover {
        background: var(--surface-hover);
        border-color: var(--accent);
    }
</style>
